0 AUGMENTATIONS AUGMENTS AUGMENT~

Augmentations are little enhancements your character can get (for a price.)
The effects of these enhancements are hidden, and do not generally show
up in the score command or in any other place, but they do affect the 
outcomes of various activities.

Here is a list of what the augments do:

Body, Head, Leg, Arm, Foot-Plating:
        These augments all protect your body from physical damage.
Body-Power:
	Increases the weight you can carry.
	Allows you to wield heavier weapons.
	Increases your chance to parry/dodge/shield block.
	Has a chance to increase your melee damage.
	Increases your ability to groundfight.
Arm-Power:
	Allows you to wield heavier weapons.
	Increases your chance to parry/dodge/shield block.
	Increases your chance to bash.
	Has a chance to increase your melee damage.
	Increases your ability to groundfight.
Hand-Power: 
	Increases your backstab damage.
	Allows you to wield heavier weapons.
	Increases your chance to parry/dodge/shield block.
	Increases your chance to land tackles.
	Has a chance to increase your melee damage.
	Increases your ability to groundfight.
Leg-Power:
	Increases the damage of kicks.
	Increases the weight you can carry.
Foot-Power:
	Increases the damage of kicks.
	Increases the weight you can carry.
Hand-Speed:
	Increases your backstab damage.
	Increases your offensive bonus (hitroll).
	Increases your chance to parry/dodge/shield block.
	Increases your chance to land tackles.
	Increases your ability to groundfight.
Leg-Speed:
	Increases your offensive bonus (hitroll).
	Increases your chance to land tackles.
	Increases your chance to dodge.
	Increases your chance to flee.
	Decreases your moves loss while moving.
	Decreases your chance to be bashed and tackled.
Foot-Speed:
	Increases your offensive bonus (hitroll).
	Increases your chance to land tackles.
	Increases your chance to dodge.
	Increases your chance to flee.
	Decreases your moves loss while moving.
	Decreases your chance to be bashed and tackled.
Mind-Power:
	Increases the damage of offensive spells.
	Increases the strength of mana shield.
	Increases mana regeneration.
	Lowers the chance for you to lose concentration on a spell.
	Lowers slightly the casting time of spells.
Mind-Focus:
	Increases the amount of healing spells.
	Increases the strength of mana shield.
	Increases mana regeneration.
	Lowers the chance for you to lose concentration on a spell.
	Lowers slightly the casting time of spells.
Face-Spike:
	Increases your damage in a groundfight.
	Adds a 1/6 chance to blind on a headbutt in groundfight.
	Adds a very rare chance to land two blows in a groundfight.
Mana-Boost:
	Adds 20 percent to your base mana.
	Increases mana regeneration.
Channeling:
        Increases your mana level, enabling you to cast higher spells.
Mental-Armor:
	Increases your chance to save against a spell's effects.
	Lowers duration of negative spell effects.
	Lowers damage slightly of enemy spells.
Focus:
	Increases the damage you can take and remain casting.
	Increases the strength of mana shield.
	Lowers the chance for you to lose concentration on a spell.
	Lowers slightly the casting time of spells.


~

0 ALIAS ALIASES MACRO MACROS~
Syntax: alias
Syntax: alias {<characters>"} {<does-this>}
Syntax: alias <number> deletes the alias.

A '*' character in an alias will be considered as if you pressed enter.
A '%' character will be translated as an argument.  For instance:

Example: alias {pb} {put % in backpack}

from now on, 'pb waterskin' would be expanded to 'put waterskin in backpack'.

Example: alias {5} {sleep}       -will make you sleep after you type: 5  <enter>
Example: alias {rs} {rest}       -will make you rest after you  type: rs <enter>
Example: alias {yum} {get bread*eat bread*smile}
Example: alias {k} {kill}

Aliases are used so you don't have to type so much.  It also enables you
to do multiple tasks such as: backstab, flee, run south. 

-Note: if you give an argument to the alias, it will use it as an argument
       to the last command in the alias.  (i.e., using the 'k'='kill'
       example, 'k bear' will come out as 'kill bear'.
~  


