0 GNOMES GNOME~
Gnomes are only about 3 feet tall and have been likened to a cross between 
an elf and a squirrel with long beards. Gnomes love a loud tavern as much as 
an open woodland, and thus can find all they desire in almost any locale. Although
they love to cause trouble, these clever little creatures also appreciate beauty and 
friendship. Many Gnomes have innate abilities to understand the speech of 
animals, and to communicate with whatever spirits happen to inhabit an area.

Since Gnomes have been known to live in small dim-litted areas they gain the ability
of Infravision.
~

0 HUMAN HUMANS ~
A human usually weights around one hundred and ninety pounds, ranging from
five feet to seven feet tall. They are average at everything, there's not
much about them that makes them special. Their capability's however can
vast far greater then any of the other races. If you have the time and
skill, a human can be a great investment.

Humans have been hiding in caves since early racial purges of their race. 
Due to their dark existance they gain the ability of infravision. It is 
also told that the Humans were the first to discover the mysteries of the
mystical shards. Since their discover they have learned to protect themselves
against these shards. Due to their ability in this, they gain the ability
of Protection from Shards.
~

0 ATOMIE ~

The Atomie is a very basic creature, it relies mostly on instinct. The 
Atomie creatures are small and very round, with strong arms and fast reflexes.
They are known to be dark creatures that live in very secluded areas. Typically
they are friendly creatures, but there are the bad bunch. Their skills make them
excellent Rogues for they have reflexas greater then most.

Due to their natural abilities to be aware of all situations, they receive the
ability of Detect-Hidden.
~

0 TROLL TROLLS ~
Trolls are large creatures, three times the mass of a man. They have dark 
brown skin nearly the color of oak bark, high elven-like cheekbones, and pointed 
ears. Trolls are extremely strong, and usually live in the wildest parts of the 
forests of the world in small clannish groups, though some have learned the ways 
of man's cities. They are very noticiable by the stench they secreat when they sweat.

Trolls genetics gain them the ability to heal quicker then normal races.

~

0 DWARF DWARVES ~
Though made lower to the ground than most races, the Dwarves created by Brell Serilis burst with pride and determination. 
The stout and sturdy Dwarves are extremely strong, making them one of the best-suited to endure long and intense battles. 
Dwarves have broad faces, usually with a prominent nose, and take extraordinary pride in their hair. Males often take great 
care to grow long beards and moustaches and females often tie their hair up in a bun. Some females also sport a finely trimmed beard.
This ancient race is strongly motivated by honor and loyalty. They also know how to balance work and play, and know how to tell a good 
story. If a Dwarf is ever wronged, it can be painful for the wrongdoer as Dwarves tend to hold a grudge. 

Due to the peacefulness of Dwarves and their love for nature, lower level creatures are less likely to attack them and gain
the ability of Safety.
~

0 DARK-ELF DARK-ELVES ~

Dark Elves are by nature a peaceful race, but since the wars of good vs. evil they have come out
of hiding to help their surroundings from being destroyed. Some have been corrupted over the
years and have gone evil and hell-bent over destruction. Dark-Elves look exactly like their
brotheren the High-Elves only their entire skin is a dark blue color due to being in caves
for centuries.

Since Dark-Elves have been inside the dark for many of years, they gain the natural ability of Infravision.
~

