0 'CAPTURE'~

Capture is a new feature in LoC. There are designated battle areas. Sapentenia 
and the Castle of Yur are the only two capture areas. Once you raid the city, 
and type "capture" at the throne room, that entire outpost becomes yours. The 
guards now pledge their allegance to your alignment. By typing "align", you will 
get a specific bonus to your alignment, whatever bonus that OP gives you. Your entire
align will have this bonus until the other alignment can capture it.
~

110 'IMMCAPTURE'~

cvnuml - will set the vnum that you want the area to be the lower number
cvnumh - will set the vnum for the area you want to be, the higher number

For example cvnuml 50000 and cvnumh 50500 will set the areas from 50000-5500
as a capture are, so when they type capture, it will change all the mobs in
those vnum lists.

cbonusstr s or i or w or d or c

Will set what attributed they get when they capture s = strength etc.

redit then type throneroom will set the room as a capturable area.
~

