0 'buildarmor'~

Here are the rules for making new equipment and items:
1.  No cheater items.  For example, a scroll that casts Ice comet that loads
    at 100 percent.  Please do not make cheater weapons for yourself unless it
    is cleared with Sabelis.
2.  There will be no items above 2 apb, 25 hp (or 15 hp if the character can wear
    two of the items), 5 hit, 25 moves (or 15 moves if the character can wear two
    of the items), 5 kick, 5 saving_throw, or 5 armor class.  Also, no item will
    have above 10 ac in one location.
3.  Kick can be on only belt, greaves, kneepad, anklet, and boots.  
4.  Head Ac should be on helmet, earring, aura, eye, face and neck.
5.  Body ac should be on about, breastplate, shoulderplate and back. 
6.  Arm ac should be on wrist, elbowpad, arms, and hands. 
7.  Leg ac should be on belt, greaves, kneepad, anklet, and boots. 
8.  A shield can be all around same with an aura. 
9.  Items with basic ac (0-3), less than 5 hp or move, less than 2 kick, and using
    your common sense on the rest should load at the highest of 30 percent.
10. Items with medium ac (4-6), less than 10 hp or move, less than 4 kick, and using
    common sense on the rest should load at a highest of 15 percent depending upon
    stats.
11. Items with heavy ac (7-10), with above 15 hp or move, 5 kick, and using common
    sense on the rest of the stats should load at a highest of 5 percent with really
    good items at 1 percent.
12. There will be no plus stat eq in the game.
13. Please use a reasonable weight for the class the item was made for.  Also, the better
    the item the more it should cost.  
~

0 'screen shot'~

How to make a picture after taking a screen shot!

If you do not know how to make a screen shot... Here is a simple helpfile.

Find out what you want to take a screen shot of. As in scroll your Zmud or
whatever telnet client you are using to what you want to take a screen shot of,
make sure no one chating or moving will ruin your screen shot.

Windows:
Once you have what you want a screen shot of, hit ptr scr or print screen key,
open up start-->programs-->accessories-->imaging.

Once imaging opens up click in top left on file. Once the drop down menu
drops down click on new.

You should get a big box in middle of the screen that says TIFF, bitmap, JPG.
click the little circle next to JPG.

Next right click in the middle of the BIG WHITE part of the screen and hit paste.

Click on file again and hit save as.. Save the file in a location easy to find.

Then open up your email program, email the screen shot to locstaff@hotmail.com
and an attachment.

Do not alter your file in ANY way.
~
